Doc Spatz,<br>
     Just a word or two.  Please DO NOT USE the term Nazi-Christian.  I won't deny some people who called themselves Christian like Franz von Papen helped Hitler get into power, but the Nazis didn't want anyone seriously practicing Christianity.  That's why Protestants like Dietrich Bonhoffer and Catholics like Maximillian Kolbe were arrested and died in the concentration camps along with the Jews.  There have always been Christians who remember Paul's words in Romans 12 and treated Jews properly as fellow human beings.<br><br>
     As for Stan; I think he forgot that Jesus followed the path of the suffering servant in Isaiah, and &quot;didn't cry out aloud in the streets or quench a flickering wick&quot;, and asked before he preached.  It would have been proper ( and I'm talking Christian etiquette here not freedom of speech ) to request permission of the site administrators.  I also don't recall the Good Samaritan asking the injured man to convert before offering help.  As a Christian I apologize for him; whether he likes it or not.
